inn1.comm: starts off with a wide delivery outside off
another widish delivery outside off, the batsman leaves it alone, the keeper takes it low around his knees
beats the batsman with one that angles across. Gambhir doesn't come fully forward in his defence and the ball  goes past his outside edge
short of length delivery outside off, cuts back in to Gambhir a touch but safely left alone
short of length, comes in to Gambhir who was leaving the  ball on length. It hits the handle of the bat and goes one bounce towards the slip cordon
gets one on his pads and he easily flicks it past square leg for the first boundary of the day. That sped across the turf
takes a big stride against a delivery that is angled across, left alone
fuller length outside off, Rohit takes a stride forward and lets it go.
another fuller delivery beats Rohit outside off. This time, instead of leaving the ball, Rohit tries to drive it. But he is not to the pitch of the ball
same length, same line wide outside off, left alone
length ball angling in to Rohit, he takes a forward stride and defends that to the leg side
seams away after pitching outside off on a length, left alone
languid elegance as Rohit comes forward to the pitched up delivery outside off and crunches a square drive through the gap on off
length ball outside off, carries on with the angle, left alone
gets squared up by a ball that cuts away after pitching on the pads, leading edge goes towards point
fuller length on off, beats Gambhir's forward prod as he doesn't really take a big stride
short of length, angled across the batsman, Gambhir shoulders arms
gets a shortish delivery around off stump, and he cuts it hard over point off the back foot for a one-bounce four
length ball just outside off, goes on with the angle, batsman lets it go through to the keeper
fuller length ball on off stump, Rohit comes forward and defends it to cover point
length ball on off, Rohit comes forward and defends it towards off with an open face

caught at second slip! So the success rate of experiment with Rohit opening has come down to 50%. It was floated outside off and Rohit attempted to drive while not really taking a big stride forward. The edge flies at a comfortable height to the right of second slip

caught at second slip! Action replay of the previous ball! Entices the new man with a floated delivery outside off, gets some away movement and Kohli, who went for the drive, edges it to Tredwell at second slip, this time to his left. Tredwell juggles it a few times before completing the catch.
oh he was late to pick that one. Fuller length delivery on the middle, swings in to Yuvraj who stays in the crease and bring the bat down in time to defend that
short of length, darts away from the batsman. Yuvraj left that ball, but he didn't read the movement there
short of length, angles across Gambhir, left alone to the keeper
138 kph, short of length ball outside off, another one left alone
length ball on off stump, Gambhir comes forward and defends it towards the off side
he keeps it accurate around off. It is short of length and Gambhir shoulders arms
length ball around off stump, cuts a touch into the batsman, left alone outside off
short ball on the body, Gambhir fends it away awkwardly towards short fine and takes a single
length ball outside off, Gambhir comes forward and drives it to mid-off
length ball with some width outside off, Gambhir stays in the crease and cracks it through cover point
fuller length delivery angling away from the batsman, left alone by the batsman
fuller length, closer to the stumps this time and Gambhir takes a forward stride and drives it straight down the ground. As beautiful as any shot
length ball on off, defended towards off
fuller length delivery on the pads, swings a bit and beats Gambhir's attempted flick, hits him on the pads and rolls towards square leg
bowls short of length angling in to Gambhir, defended towards off side off the back foot
another short of length delivery angling in, he tries to whip it away to the leg side, but gets hit on the pads as it bounces extra
beaten outside off with one that seams away after pitching. Gambhir was on the backfoot and fishes for that ball outside off
short of length on the body, bounces extra and is awkwardly fended off toward the leg side

caught at point! Oh, it is another one gone! Yuvraj tries to flick a length delivery on the middle stump but doesn't really take the movement in the ball into account. The leading edge flies straight to point and the batsman is left looking ugly.
short delivery and Raina gets hit around the chest area. He was too slow in his attempt to sway away from the line, the ball follows him.
quick delivery, but full and wide outside off, Gambhir stretches out and gets beaten in his drive
half-volley on off stump and Gambhir takes a forward stride and drives it through the off side. It keeps the fielder interested but gets to the boundary
short of length on the pads, turned towards fine leg for a single
fuller length delivery, swinging in to Raina and hits the pads, but that was heading down the leg side
looks for swing on off stump with a full delivery, Raina comes forward and drives that to mid-on
length delivery on the pads, not much swing in that one and Raina wrists it from the middle stump line down to deep backward square boundary
length ball on the middle stump line, defended towards midwicket off the back foot by Gambhir
hops and turns that off the hips towards fine-leg for a single
that almost carried back to the bowler! It was a length ball and Raina drives it on the up, it just bounces in front of the bowler
angles this one away from a short of length, left alone by the batsman
short of length on the pads, Raina flicks it in the air past the leg gully fielder who has just been placed there before the ball
angling delivery from round the stumps, the batsman lets it go. Some oohs and aahs as it wasn't too far from the off stump
length delivery on off stump, Raina gets behind the line and defends it back towards the bowler
back of length on the middle stump, turned away straight to midwicket off the back foot
fuller length delivery on off, Raina comes forward and drives it hard back to the bowler
short of length on the off stump, defended to mid-off
this one goes away after pitching and beats Raina outside off as he tries to play at that one away from the body
dropped at second slip! length delivery outside off, Raina goes for the drive and edges it low to the left of Tredwell, who gets a hand to it but can't quite complete the catch
short of length and it's almost cut straight to the hands of Morgan at point. Just drops cms short of the fielder
now beats the batsman outside off. Gambhir was playing for the angle, but the ball moved a touch away after pitching short of off
he is not reading the movement at all. This one came in with the angle, but Gambhir left it alone and it goes past the off stump
a touch shorter in length outside off, allows Gambhir time to read and he leaves it alone
length ball, wide outside off, left alone by the batsman
completes a maiden by sticking around the off stump line, left alone by the batsman
it is short of length, but it is outside leg stump and Raina hops and plays it fine down to the fine-leg boundary
a big positive stride on  a length delivery outside off, drives it through extra cover from the middle of his bat
133 kph, length ball just outside off, Raina watches the line carefully and lets it go
swings in to the batsman after pitching on length on off, he tries to play it from the crease and inside edges it to deep backward square. 4000 runs for Raina
short of length delivery on off, defended towards the leg side
gets a short and wide freebie outside off, he stays on the back foot and slams it past point for yet another boundary
floated on off stump, defended back to the bowler

cut to point! Gambhir gets some room outside off and crashes it towards the point region where Ian Bell dives to his left to swoop a low catch and send Gambhir packing. It was not a good delivery to start with and the shot was on, but Gambhir paid the price of playing it in the air
flighted on off stump, Dhoni takes a forward stride and places it in the gap at midwicket
big turn for Tredwell! It was a flatter delivery angled into the batsman, it grips the surface and goes past the outside edge
this one goes on straight and takes the inside edge before hitting him on the pad
comes down the track to a flatter delivery but has to awkwardly defend that towards off as the ball turns after pitching
full swinging delivery outside off, Dhoni comes right forward and plays a bottom-handed drive through cover point

this one is closer to the stumps and didn't swing at all. Dhoni played outside the line of the ball and gets hit on the pads. The appeal is turned down as it hit him outside off; Dhoni had shuffled across quite a lot
short of length on off, defended off the back foot
stays on the crease and drops the short of length ball dead on the pitch
stays on the crease and pushes the length ball on off back towards the bowler
length ball outside off, Raina comes forward and pushes it straight past the non-striker. KP at mid-off runs across to his left and dives to keep the batsmen to a single
tossed up delivery outside off, Raina comes forward and pushes it towards the gap at cover and takes a quick single
pushed through outside off, Dhoni defends it back to the bowler from the crease
floated up to the batsman, on off, turned towards midwicket
he comes across and tries to play that towards leg side, gets hit on the pads, but it hit him outside the line of off
tossed up on off, turned away to midwicket fielder
takes a forward stride and plays the ball with spin towards midwicket
it is down the leg side and is called a wide
length ball wide outside off, Raina doesn't get lured by that one, leaves it alone
short of length on off stump, defended towards mid-on off the back foot
length ball on off, the batsman stays in the crease and defends it to cover
length ball goes across the batsman, Raina lets it go through to the keeper
quick short ball and Raina tries to play a hook, but he has head has already fallen off and the ball goes past his helmet
length ball on off, driven on the up but straight to cover
flighted on off stump, Dhoni takes a forward step and works it with the spin towards deep backward square
pushed through outside off, Raina defends it towards midwicket and steals single
tries to play an expansive sweep but misses the ball, he gets hit on the pads but the impact was outside the line of off
defends the flighted delivery on off to midwicket
flatter delivery on off, goes straight on, defended on the back foot
comes down the pitch and pushes this flighted delivery on off to long on
length ball outside off, Dhoni gets square up a bit as the ball seam away a touch, the outside edge takes the ball to third man
length ball on off, Raina takes a forward step and pushes it to the left of extra cover, calls for a quick single
length ball on off, Dhoni shuffles across and defends it back to the bowler
short delivery on the leg stump, Dhoni swivels and pulls it down to deep backward square
length ball angled across the left hander, left alone
length ball on the pads, Raina flicks it easily towards deep square leg
pushed through on off stump, Raina goes back and pushes it towards cover
comes forward to this slow and tossed up delivery on off, defended back to the bowler
flatter outside off, driven to cover off the front foot
quicker delivery on off, defended off the backfoot
he takes care of the flight this time by coming down the pitch quickly and launching it straight over the sightscreen
flighted outside off stump, Raina comes forward and covers the line of the ball, then lets it go through
short of length delivery outside off, cuts away from Dhoni and he gets beaten as he tries to play that off the back foot
fuller length delivery outside off, left alone by the batsman
shuffled across to play that from outside off towards midwicket for a single
fuller length ball, goes across the left-hander, left alone by Raina
short delivery on off stump, Raina goes back and drops it to the left of the midwicket fielder and calls for a quick single
fuller length delivery outside off and Dhoni doesn't walk across this time, instead takes a forward stride and drives it through cover
flighted delivery on off stump, the batsman comes forward and defends
slower, tossed up outside off, it grips and turns, left alone by the batsman
that was a quicker one on the middle stump and Raina gets square up in his attempt to turn that to the leg side
width outside off, it's short too, punched to deep point off the back foot
flighted on off stump, Dhoni takes a forward stride and turns it to square leg
jumps out of the crease but can't get under that flatter one, drives it flat to long on

Cook's plan to bring back Finn has made impact immediately. It was length ball angling in to Dhoni and the batsman had walked across, as he has been doing, to play that towards the leg side. But Finn is quick and he beats Dhoni's attempted flick, hits him in front of middle..
beats the batsman outside off, it is a quick delivery, it pitches on a length and goes across the batsman
a bit wide outside off on  a length, easily left alone
short of length delivery outside off, Jadeja gets out of the line, but not very convincingly
length ball across the batsman, Jadeja plays down the wrong line and is beaten
short of length, angles across the batsman, left alone by the batsman
flighted on the middle stumps, the batsman goes down on his knee and sweeps to deep square leg
flighted outside off, defended back to the bowler
quicker and flatter delivery on the pads, flicked to deep backward square leg off the back foot
shout for lbw as the batsman gets beaten in his forward defence, the ball was sliding down leg
flighted on the pads, dabbed towards square leg
flatter delivery on the off stump, Raina comes forward and defends
length ball on off stump, Jadeja comes forward and drives it back to the bowler
fuller delivery on the pads, swings in a bit, but Jadeja tried to flick it after walking across and misses, the ball hits the pads and rolls to the right of the keeper
length ball outside off, carries on with the angle, left alone
he gets beaten by one that cut back into him! It was on a length outside off and the batsman went forward to defend, but the ball cut in and went past the inside edge
shorter length outside off, the batsman stays back and cuts it to third-man
fuller delivery on off stump, the batsman comes forward and drives it hard, but straight to mid-off
flatter delivery on the off stump line, the batsman comes forward and defends
flighted delivery outside off, takes the outside edge and it goes past Cook at first slip as the batsman stretches out to play at that one, the ball runs down to the boundary
quicker delivery on the stumps, the batsman gets cramped for room as he goes back to play a cut
takes a forward stride and drives the ball to long-on
fired on the pads, the batsman turns it to midwicket
inside edge saves Raina this time. It was flatter on off and Raina plays outside the line, the ball takes an inside edge before hitting the pads

is that out down the leg side? Not out given. The batsman tries to flick the short of length delivery, but misses. It hits his thigh pad and goes through to the keeper. Steve Davis says not out immediately. Good decision
length ball outside off, the batsman leaves it on the angle
that is closer to the off stump on a length, the batsman comes forward and defends it to off
short of length delivery on off stump, Jadeja goes back and runs it down to third-man
short of length outside off, Raina defends it towards cover from the crease
length ball on off, Raina goes back and pushes the ball towards mid-on with soft hands, calls for a single
comes down the track but realises he is nowhere near the pitch of the ball, has to takes defensive action
quicker on the pads, Raina stays back and works it to square leg
flighted delivery on off, Jadeja drives it to long-on
he sees the flight early and comes down the pitch to launch the ball for his second six over the sightscreen
gets a quick short delivery in response and he goes back and punches it to deep cover for a single
drawn forward on a flighted ball outside off, he plays it to the left of point for another single
length ball outside off, angling away from the left hander, left alone by Jadeja
fuller length outside off, Jadeja takes a forward stride and drives it to mid-off
gets beaten by a short of length delivery outside off as he tries to throw his bat at that one, away from his body
length ball on the middle stump, the batsman stays in the crease and turns it to deep midwicket
length delivery on off stump, Raina gets close to the pitch of the ball and drives, but straight to mid-off
short of length on off and middle, the batsman tucks it to the left of midwicket fielder and steals a single
takes a forward stride to a length ball and drives it to extra cover
flighted delivery on off, Raina has to come forward to defend that back to the bowler
tossed up, but a touch outside off this time, the batsman pushes it towards the gap at cover point
goes back to a tossed up delivery and has to play that back to the bowler after the ball turns away
this one slides in to the batsman and he gets beaten, hit on the pads
keeps it tight on the off and middle line, defended off the front foot
touch fuller and the batsman takes a single by driving to long on
tossed up outside off, the batsman comes forward and drives it straight down the ground. Long-on does the fielding
fligted delivery, pushed to long on for another single
tossed up on the middle stump line, the batsman works it to deep square leg off the front foot
outside off this time and Raina dabs it to the left of short point for a single
another six straight over the sightscreen, this time by Jadeja. He came down the pitch and just lifted a flighted delivery over the bowler' head
now plays with soft hands towards cover and takes a single
draws Jadeja out with a flighted delivery outside off, the batsman misses and the keeper takes the bails off in a flash. The replays show that the batsman had just pushed his toe back in the line.
flatter on the middle stump line, defended to the leg side
full and flat on off stump, pushed to long-on off the front foot
slower and flighted on off stump, the batsman defends it to cover off the front foot
flatter delivery on the middle stump, pushed to long-on
comes forward and plays it to midwicket
flighted delivery on off stump, defended towards off, the fielder at cover point cuts off the single
tossed up delivery is driven down the ground to long-off
fuller and quicker on the middle, Jadeja takes his front foot out of the way and drives it to long on
flatter delivery and Raina completes his fourth consecutive fifty with a chip over extra cover after he moved a bit outside leg
rotates the strike by pushing it to long-off
fuller and flatter, driven down to long-on
pushed through on off stump, slight turn, defended towards cover off the front foot
quicker slider on off and middle, defended from the crease
flighted on off stump line, the batsman stretches out and defends
slower through the air, on off stump line, defended towards point off the front foot
opens the face of the bat as he defends it towards off
drives this fuller delivery on off and middle  to midwicket
slower delivery on off stump, the batsman waits for it and turns it towards backward square leg to takes a single
flatter delivery on off, defended towards the leg side, the batsman think about a single but then decide against it
goes back to cut the ball, but is not able to beat the fielder at point
pushed through on off, defended back to the bowler
gets after Root with a charged down loft over the sightscreen to the first tier
flatter delivery on off, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot
he comes down the track aiming for the boundary around cow corner, but he is not able to get to the pitch of the ball and ends up dragging that to deep midwicket
flatter delivery on off, Jadeja opens the face to play it to point
comes down the track but is not to the pitch of the ball, defends with pad and bat close together
pushed to the leg side, around midwicket off a flatter delivery for a single
thinks of coming down the track, but the bowler bowls it short and quick, Raina has to defend
flatter delivery outside off, defended towards the off side
pitches it on a length outside the leg stump, the batsman tucks it away to deep backward square region for a single
short of length on the middle and leg line, the batsman stays back and plays it towards short fine leg
slower bouncer, but it is outside the leg stump. Jadeja spots that and rolls his wrists as he pulls that down to fine leg
gets width with this short of length delivery outside off, he just had to beat point there and he gets the placement right
length ball on the pads, flicked off the back foot towards deep backward square leg
short delivery on the middle and Jadeja is slow on his pull shot, he underedges it on to his body
quicker delivery but he bowls that down the leg side

dropped by Cook! Oh Raina gets another reprieve! It was a shorter, quicker delivery on the middle and he tries to plays a loose pull, the ball goes to the right of Cook, who dives and gets two hands to it, but palms it away
flatter delivery on the middle, played towards midwicket
drives it in the air and this time Tredwell himself drops it. Well he got his right hand to it
he comes down the wicket and hits it to deep midwicket along the ground
plays off the back foot to the right of backward point
flatter delivery, defended back to the bowler of the front foot
full delivery wide of off stump, Raina comes forward and drives to deep backward point
short of length on the middle stump line, flicked to deep square leg off the back foot
gets a slower bouncer, but it is outside leg stump and Raina attempts a pull but makes no contact
another shorter delivery on the body, Raina plays the pull towards deep midwicket
short of length delivery on the pads, turned down to fine leg off the back foot by Jadeja
fuller length on middle and leg stump, the batsman stays on the crease and pushes it to mid-on
half-volley outside off and Raina drives, but he hits it straight to extra cover
goes on the back foot and drag the ball from off and middle to deep midwicket
quick ball sliding down the leg side, the batsman misses the sweep shot
flatter delivery just outside off, the batsman waits and plays it towards point with soft hands

caught at point! Charges down the track to a flatter delivery and wanted to hit that over long-on, but there is some turn, enough for the ball to take a thick outside edge and lob to the fielder at point.
flatter, quicker on the off stump, turns into the batsman, defended towards the leg side off the back foot
flighted on off, the batsman comes forward to defend
short of length delivery on the middle, comes in a touch into the batsman, who gets hit on the thigh pad and the ball rolls to the off side
short of length delivery on off stump, he stays in the crease and tucks it towards midwicket for a single
goes back and punches a back of length delivery outside off towards the left of cover
136 kph, short of length delivery on off, bounces more than the batsman anticipates, defended on off
length delivery on off, seams away after pitching, the batsman gets a leading edge towards off as he tries to play that to leg side
going down the wrong line, on the pads. It is short of length and hits Ashwin's thigh pad as he tries to whip it
tossed up delivery on off, turned away to deep midwicket
takes a couple of steps down the track and smears this flatter delivery to the left of deep midwicket
comes down the pitch again but gets under the ball better this time, it goes straight into the gap between long-on and deep midwicket
it is a shorter delivery outside off, turns in into Raina, who plays a pull to deep midwicket
stays in the crease and pushes the flatter delivery on long-on
flatter and shorter on off stump, the batsman goes right back and punches it to wide long-off for a single
short of length on the leg stump line, Raina charges down but gets cramped as he plays the pull towards deep midwicket
short of length outside off and Ashwin stays in the crease and whips it away to deep square leg easily
length ball on the pads, Raina stays in the crease and flicks it to deep backward square leg for a couple

caught at midwicket! Raina has pulled the short of length delivery straight to Bell at the edge of the circle at midwicket. It was a slower delivery and that is what put Raina off his shot probably, normally he hits them quite well.  How important is that wicket for England! Raina was India's last recognised batsman.
length ball on off stump line, driven to mid-off
length ball outside off, the batsman watches it carefully and lets it go
on the pads and Ashwin is not able to get it away, gets hit on the pads
slightly shorter on off, the batsman goes back and punches it to the left of extra cover
flatter delivery on off, defended down the pitch
pushed through on off, the batsman punches it down to long-on
now Ashwin punches it to long-on for a single
Tredwell is kept busy at long-on with another single being taken in that area
seams away after pitching just outside off on a length, Bhuvi tries to play it off the back foot and is beaten
bowls fuller on middle stump, the batsman stays in the crease and defends it to off side
short and wide, Bhuvi cuts is hard for his first boundary through point. That was not very far from the backward point fielder though
gets squared up by one that cuts away from a length, edges it to the left of third-man
the batsman walks down the pitch, but Woakes adjusts his length to bowl it short, defended to the leg side
length ball on off stump, pushed through to the left of midwicket
pushed through on the middle, defended off the front foot
flatter outside off, some turn, he whips it to the leg side, but straight to mid-on
on the off stump, turns a bit, defended to off with an open face
quicker delivery on the off, defended off the back foot
makes room by moving outside leg and cuts the flat delivery to deep cover
he gets down on his knee, outside off and laps this fuller delivery to the left of short fine leg, but it doesn't go too far
shorter delivery on the middle and Ashwin pulls it comfortably, for a couple, to deep backward square
tries to whip another short of length delivery from the crease, but misses and gets hit on the pads, the batsmen run leg byes
short of length outside off, the batsman stays on the back foot and defends it to point
he is been playing lot of defensive shots but now he gets another short and wide one, and he cashes in by thumping it hard to deep point boundary
in the channel outside off, defended towards point off the back foot
angling in to the pads from back of length, tucked away to midwicket for a single
makes room by moving down the pitch and plays an inside out drive over cover
flatter delivery on the middle stump, he turns it to square leg
goes for a sweep but is not able to beat the fielder at short fine

comes down the pitch and goes through with the lofted shot even though he was not to the pitch of it. It goes very high and Tredwell gets a hand to it at the edge of the long-on boundary, but is not able to control it. It pops out and over the line
this time he gets his sweep shot right and plays it hard to deep backward square leg boundary

caught at square leg! tries to sweep again but the ball is flat and short. He ends up half-pulling, half-sweeping, the ball takes a top edge and lobs towards square leg and Finn, running around from short fine, takes an easy catch
length ball on the middle, but Bhuvi has made room by moving outside leg stump (a bit like Zaheer Khan) and thumps it straight over the bowler's head for a boundary
he bowls a slower bouncer outside off, the batsman waits but is unable to get any bat on that one
get a quick short ball on the body, the batsman takes his eyes off as he fends it somehow to the leg side
another bouncer, this time outside off, it is quick and it goes over the batsman's attempted waft at it
back of length on the middle stump line, defended back to the bowler off the back foot
another slower bouncer outside off, the batsman waits and tries to upper cut it, but makes no contact
short of length on the middle stump line, the batsman arches back and tries to run it down past point, but plays it straight to the fielder
makes room and toe-ends the length ball over the infield at cover, the fielder from deep cover, Root, runs around and makes a sliding stop to prevent the boundary
he follows the batsman as he makes room, but Bhuvi manages to cut it to third man
fuller delivery outside off, Shami moves his front foot out to play a forceful drive, but straight to mid-off
short of length, coming into the batsman who gets cramped for room, played toward midwicket for a single

dropped by Samit Patel at cover Shami tries to smash the ball out of the ground but manages a top-edge which comes down towards short cover. Patel runs in from extra cover and slides in, gets there, and drops a dolly
short of length outside off, it gets big on him, but in this Grand Slam season, he shows his forehand and hits it to deep midwicket boundary

caught at mid-off! Bhuvi's little cameo  comes to an end as he only manages to get a toe-end of the bat at this slower delivery outside off. Finn, at mid-off, shows how it is done by running in and diving forward to complete a good low catch
bowls it full and wide outside the marker, called a wide
quick bouncer gives Bresnan his fourth! It was too quick for Shami, who tries to pull the ball, but gets a top edge on to the helmet and it then just lobs up for the bowler to complete the catch

inn2.comm: pitches on leg stump and swings away from the left-hander. Cook stays on the back foot to play at that but misses
length ball outside off, swings further away and this time it is safely left alone
similar delivery to the first one, a touch short maybe, it catches the outside edge and goes through where third slip could have been
shorter in length outside off, the batsman tries to cut it, but there is not much room and he dabs it towards point
beats Cook again with one that leaves the left-hander. Cook stayed rooted on the crease and tried to flay that one through off
this one swings the other way after pitching outside leg. But Cook does well to get his bat down in time as he defends on the leg side
the batsman leaves the ball assuming it was going to swing away, but it goes just past the off stump. Close.
fuller delivery around off stump, shapes away from the batsman, Bell doesn't move his feet and tries to drive it, gets a thick inside edge to fine leg
length delivery, pitches on the middle, shaping into the left-hander, Cook defends it to midwicket
too full and a bit wide outside off stump, no problems for the batsman in leaving it alone
138 kph, another full delivery outside off, Cook resists and lets it go.
another length delivery outside off, keeps angling away from the left-hander, Cook leaves it alone
short of length delivery outside off, moves away after pitching, Bell spots it and lets it go through
another one in the channel outside off, slight away movement, Bell keeps his bat away from the line
there comes the inswinger. Bell tries to play that towards the leg side, but the movement beats the bat and he gets hit on the thigh pad
length ball wide of off, swings away after pitching, Bell watches that one go through to the keeper
128 kph, in the channel outside off again, shapes away a touch, left alone by the batsman
he completes his maiden by bowling that teasing line outside off. Bell doesn't bother going after it
beats Cook with a beautiful delivery! It was full on off stump and Cook expected it to swing back into him. He tried to play that without any feet movement, the ball goes straight through
short of length on the pads, Cook stays back and tucks it down to fine leg off his hips
short of length just outside off, shapes away a touch. Bell waits for the movement and gets behind it to defend it to the off side
loses direction as he pushes this one down the leg side, it swings further and is called a wide
137 kph, he gets an inside edge which goes past his stumps to the fine leg boundary. Bell tried to play the short of length delivery, but he didn't move his feet at all
shortish delivery on the stumps, the batsman gets hit on the thigh pad and the ball rolls to the leg side
138 kph, length ball angling away from the left-hander, left alone
keeps testing Bell with length ball outside off. This one shapes away and Bell lets it go
he spots the length, which is a bit fuller, and goes through with a square drive with an open face, covering the swing very well
short of length on off stump, Bell goes right behind the line and defends it down the pitch off the back foot
another good outswinger. It pitches short of length outside off, and then leaves the batsman. Bell watches it go through to the keeper
takes small steps down the pitch but leaves the ball realising it is wide of off
keeps a tight line outside off and continues to bowl his outswingers, Bell leaves it alone
length ball on off stump, defended off the front foot to the off side
short of length and it's on the pads, Cook stands tall and punches it through square leg easily
136 kph, length ball swinging away from the left-hander, Cook leaves it alone after seeing it is outside off
length delivery, goes across the batsman, he leaves it alone
length ball swinging into the left-hander, Cook punches it to mid-on
he goes for a drive to this fuller delivery wide of off, doesn't get it off the middle, but puts enough behind it to get a boundary through cover
he continues to keep it in the channel and Bell continues to stay patient, leaves it alone
oh beautifully timed through cover! It was a length ball wide outside off and Bell gets on his toes and punches it off the back foot to the cover boundary
pulls the length back and keeps it outside off, left alone by the batsman
it is another inside edge, but Dhoni gets a hand to it and the slip fielders run around to pull it back. It was short outside off and Bell went for a loose cut
length ball in the channel, consistent seam movement away from the batsman, Bell keeps his bat away
length ball, a bit wide and swings away further, Bell leaves it alone

there is an appeal for caught behind first ball, but Umpire Asnani doesn't budge at all! The ball was short of length on the middle stump line, cuts back into the batsman and goes between the bat and pad to the keeper. There was a sound, probably the ball hitting the thigh pad.
short of length delivery on off stump, defended to the off side
length ball outside off, carries on with the angle, left alone by the keeper
short of length, gives some width, and Cook stays on the back foot and crashes it through cover point off the back foot
length ball just outside off, keeps going away with the angle, Cook stays well out of the line
on the off stump line this time, Cook stays on the back foot and pushes it back to the bowler
he keeps it there in the channel, Bell keeps his bat out of the way
this one angles in to the batsman, but is still outside off, a good leave by Bell who watches it go all the way to the keeper
tries to cut the short of the length delivery, but it was too close to cut and the ball takes a thick outside edge through gully and to the third-man boundary
length ball on off stump, Bell comes forward and pushes it to mid-off
he continues to make good judgments about the line of the ball as he leaves this length ball outside off

stands tall on the back foot to play this short of length delivery and just pushes it in the gap at extra cover, the balls picks up speed after crossing the fielder and runs through to the boundary. Excellent shot
short of good length on off, Cook stays on the back foot and punches it to point
gets beaten outside the off as the ball stays a touch low than what the batsman would have expected. He went for a cut shot but the ball went under the bat
fuller length outside off, Cook takes a step forward, covers the line and lets it go
140ks, fuller length, keeps it outside the channel, left alone by the batsman
length ball, angles across the left-hander. Cook stays patient and lets it go
length ball on off, Cook comes forward and defends it to cover
bowls the indipper outside the off stump, Bell gets behind solidly and defends off the back foot
it angles in from wide of the crease and straightens a bit, Bell does well to wait for that and opens the face to run it down to third-man
another outside edge past the slips! There is no second slip this time, he would have swallowed that. Cook tried to cut one which was not too short and not too wide
length ball on off, Cook comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
swings down the leg side, hits Cook's pads on its way to the fine-leg boundary
overcorrect by bowling it wide of off, it is called a wide
he come forward and drives the length ball on off through cover, but there is a deep cover in place and he keeps the batsmen to a single
length ball angling across the batsman, but Cook comes forward positively and drives it to the off side, Raina makes a good diving stop
short of length on off and middle, cuts a touch back into Cook and he gets an inside edge on to his pads
this one stays low after pitching around good length, it beats the bat as Cook tries to punch it to the off side
beats Cook with a good length delivery which keeps going across the batsman's forward prod

he has knocked the middle stump back! It was on a good length area and cuts back into the batsman just enough. Cook was neither forward nor backward and paid the price as he missed the line of the ball to lose his middle. Ishant is pumped and Cook, for once, is not lbw.
fuller length delivery, 139 ks, KP comes well forward and drives it to mid-off
bowls length, 133ks, and moves it into the right-hander in the air, Bell stays in the crease and defends it to the leg side
136 ks, short of length delivery on the stumps, Bell tries to play that on the on side but gets beaten for pace and is hit on the thigh pad
short of length on a tight line outside off, Bell stands tall and defends it towards midwicket

throws a bait by bowling a full and wide outswinger and Bell comes forward to drive, gets a thick outside edge past point. Yuvraj at third-man almost makes a meal out of it, but keeps the batsmen to two
short of length on the pads, Bell stays on the back foot and tucks it down to fine leg
short of length outside off, left alone by the batsman
now he beats Bell outside off with a delivery that straightens outside off, Bell expected it to come in with the angle, but it leaves him after pitching
keeps it there in the channel outside off, Bell stays away from the ball this time, lets it go
fuller delivery outside off, left alone by Bell
short of length outside off, doesn't do much but it's that channel which keeps the bowlers in the game, Bell stays out.
fuller length delivery angling in to the batsman, Bell comes forward and defends it solidly to the off side
short and wide outside off, Bell makes a loose attempt at cutting the ball, but it didn't bounce much and went past the outside edge
short of length on off, KP stands on his toes and punches it to mid-off
fuller length on off and middle, wobbles a bit in the air, KP stays in the crease and defends it towards the leg side
oh that is a KP special, for just a single though. It was short and KP pulls it hard off the front foot to deep midwicket, where Jadeja almost get pushed by the momentum on the ball
back of length on the middle, defended off the back foot
waits for the ball outside off and chops the short of length delivery down to third-man
fuller delivery on off stump, swings away a bit, the batsman comes forward and lets it go through
fuller length wide outside off, goes straight on, Bell stays out of the line and lets it go
he gets an inside edge on to his boots, the ball drop to the off side and the batsmen run through for a quick single
he gets beaten by one that straightens outside off. KP didn't really move in the direction of the ball and ended up driving away from the body
short of length outside off, KP watches it go through to the keeper
the fielder was surprised by the power in KP's shot! It was length and he latched on to it by coming forward and driving on the up, that went through the fielder to the extra cover boundary
he pulls the length back after that shot but keeps it in the channel, left alone by the batsman
length ball outside off, Bell comes forward and and defends it back to the bowler
another length ball outside off, it nips away in the air, Bell lets it go through to the keeper
angles into the right-hander this time, it is length ball on the off stump, Bell comes forward and pushes it to mid-on
136 ks, short of length delivery on off stump, Bell stays back and defends it to off
bowls a teasing outswinger outside off, and Bell 'the zen' leaves it alone
bowls it closer to the stumps, and the batsman comes forward and pushes it to the off side
pushed through on the middle stump, it is punched/whipped to long-on
keeps it flat outside off, Bell defends off the back foot to the off side
flatter and angling outside off, Bell goes back and opens the face very late, but straight to short third-man
flighted delivery on the off stump, Bell stays on the back foot and defends
quicker delivery on the middle stump line, Bell tucks it to square leg
tossed up and full, Bell comes forward and drives it back to the bowler

caught at deep midwicket! Shami attempts a short ball and it was slightly quicker too. KP instinctively went for a pul, but that bounced a touch more than he anticipated, and he doesn't get hold of that shot. Jadeja runs around from deep midwicket to take a good running catch close to the boundary. Big blow for  England
length ball on the pads, Ian 'quickhands' Bell flicks it to deep square leg for a couple
another length ball on middle and leg, and Bell gets outside the line and glances it fine down to fine-leg boundary
length ball wide outside off, left alone easily
he is bowling it down the leg side in this over, this one goes down too far
short of length delivery on the off stump line, defended off the back foot to the bowler
a beautiful delivery to end the over, it comes in in the air, then leaves the batsman after pitching. Luckily, it was well outside off and Bell manages to stay away
flighted delivery on off stump, the batsman comes forward and defends
flighted delivery outside off that goes straight on, Root plays inside the line expecting the ball to turn
he is not sure of whether to go forward or stay back, but manages to defend it to the leg side
comes down the pitch and flicks the tossed up delivery past midwicket for a single
flighted delivery on the off and middle line, defended off the back foot
it's flighted and it's wide of off, maybe an attempted carrom ball, Bell goes back and cuts it to sweeper cover
back of length delivery on off, Joe Root stands tall and punches it to the cover fielder
length ball outside off, Root is slow to come forward and plays it to the leg side with a closed face
length ball on off, he comes forward and drives it on the up to the cover fielder
tempts the batsman with a floater wide of off, the batsman comes right forward and pushes it to the cover fielder
sees the batsman shuffle at the crease and bowls it down the leg side
length ball outside off, Root plays with an open face, to point
drifts on to the pads, but Root misses his shot and gets hit on the thigh pad
flighted outside off and it turns into the batsman, hits the top of his pads and lobs up behind the keeper
tossed up delivery on off, defended off the front foot
pushed through, Bell  punches it back to the bowler
pushed through on the middle stump, defended to midwicket
flighted on the off and middle, he takes a forward stride and drives it to deep midwicket
tossed up and full on the middle, Root closes the face of the bat and places it past midwicket
back of length on off stump line, Root stays in the crease and defends it to the leg side
gets some width outside off and he cuts it through point between the point and gully fielder for his first boundary
back of length delivery on off stump, defended back to the bowler
back of length delivery on off, Root pushes it to cover point off the back foot
it takes an edge, but it's a hard chance for Dhoni who is standing up to the bowler, it goes through to the third-man boundary
back of length delivery on off stump, Root goes back and flicks it to deep backward square leg for a couple
pushed through on off, he goes to the back foot and turns it to backward square leg
flighted delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and drives it to long on
a touch shorter and Bell goes back and dabs it to the left of point
flighted delivery outside off, the batsman comes forward and defends
flatter and quicker on off, punched back to the bowler
stays back to this lower trajectory delivery, defended to the leg side off the back foot
defends the length ball outside off to the cover, but Kohli cuts down the possibility of a single
fuller length delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and defends
fuller delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and pushes it softly to the left of mid-off for a quick single
length ball outside off, it's pushed in the gap at cover and Kohli makes another diving stop to prevent the single
length ball in the channel, the batsman comes forward and plays that towards point with an open face
fuller length delivery on off stump, pushed to mid-on off the front foot
pushed through outside off, punched towards cover off the front foot
flighted on the middle stump line, defended back to the bowler
short and down the leg side, Bell dispatches that easily through the deep midwicket area
another short, but slightly quicker delivery, Bell goes back and plays it along the ground to deep midwicket (he just came in)
more short filth from Yuvraj, this time outside off, and Bell cuts it hard in the air fine through gully for another boundary
flatter delivery on the off and middle line, Root defends off the back foot
gets some turn immediately with a flatter delivery on off, Bell plays it down off front foot
length ball on off stump, pushed to cover off the front foot
slightly slower on off stump, Bell gets square up in his defence
he stays beside the line of the ball and defends this one towards the off side
quicker delivery, slides in with the arm, Bell digs it out off the back foot
fuller delivery on the middle and leg line, Bell gets an inside edge to square leg for a single
slower, and tossed up on off, defended off the front foot
pushed further to the batsman, on the middle line, Bell drives it to the wide long on
flatter delivery outside off, punched to deep cover off the back foot
tries to give it a lot of air, but it's a full toss and the batsman drives it to wide long-on for a couple
fuller delivery on off, the batsman completes his fifty with a little push to long-off
full and flighted, driven off the front foot by Root to long-off
flatter trajectory, on off stump, defended off the front foot
gets some width and the batsman drives it to deep cover
wanted to drive that through off, but hits it off the inside half back to the bowler
this one turns and bounces past the outside edge, Dhoni takes the bails off, but the batsman was in
pushed up to the batsman, the batsman comes forward and drives it to long-off
stays on the back foot and defends this delivery to the off side
tossed up on off stump, pushed through to long-on for a single
utter filth! It was the carrom ball, short and going down the leg side, Root just helps it on its way to the fine-leg boundary with a powerful pull
tossed up delivery on off and middle, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up offbreak outside off, comes in after pitching, the batsman makes room and places it towards deep point
he comes forward and defends the flighted delivery back down the pitch
flatter delivery on the middle stump, punched to midwicket off the back foot
flatter delivery, it's turned to deep midwicket for a couple
tossed up delivery, the batsman comes forward and plays it with an open face through gully
pushed through outside off, left alone by the batsman
fuller delivery outside off, Bell drives but Raina makes a tumbling stop at cover
quicker on the off stump line, punched back to the bowler
tossed up outside off, it doesn't turn much and beats the outside edge of the batsman
flatter delivery on off, pushed to midwicket
tossed up delivery on off stump, defended back to the bowler
he sweeps this time, down to deep backward square
flatter delivery on off stump, tucked away to deep square leg off the back foot
quicker delivery hits the pads, but it was fired down the leg side.
fuller delivery on off stump, pushed back to the bowler
gets some width outside off, Bell punches it to deep extra cover off the back foot
pushed up to the batsman, defended off the front foot
he lashes as soon as he sees the width, but there is a fielder at deep cover
punched back down the ground, but Jadeja makes a diving stop towards right to stop runs
this time he stops the ball with his left hand to prevent the single
short delivery on off stump, comes a bit quicker on to Root, but he manages to pull it to deep midwicket
effortlessly driven over the bowler's head after he charged down the pitch. It goes all the way, so good was the timing. Looked like a chip, but went all the way
turns down the leg side and is called a wide
full and flighted outside off, driven down the ground to long-on
full and flat on the leg stump, defended towards square leg
a touch shorter on off stump, punched to deep cover off the back foot
stays on the back foot and plays a late cut towards backward point for a single
width from the bowler, Bell cracks it past point for a couple. Gambhir makes a half-stop at point
short and wide, Bell's cut goes fine on the off side, down to third-man
short of length on off stump, Root tries to cut it off the back foot but is cramped for room, chops it to point
doesn't come on the bat as he tries to cut off the back foot, chops it towards backward point
a bit short outside off, but Root chooses to pull it on the leg side, it's picked up at deep midwicket boundary by Jadeja
short and wide and again Root fails to take advantage, again chops it on to the off side
pushed through on the pads, hits the batsman as he misses his flick
flatter on off and middle, punched back to the bowler
a touch fuller on off, the batsman takes a forward step and drives it down to long-off

oh no! Root goes for an uncharacteristic cross-batted shot and he misses. Jadeja normally keeps it a touch short of length and  Root didn't get to the pitch of the ball in his sweep, he misses and Jadeja hits off. Immediate impact.
flighted delivery outside off, comes in to Morgan, driven down to long-on
pushed through outside off, Bell goes back and punches it to deep cover for a single
fuller length delivery on off, beautifully driven down the ground but he is unable to beat mid-on
fuller delivery on off, Morgan drives it in the air to the off side, drops short of Rahane at cover point
pulls the length back and immediately beats the batsman as Morgan plays inside the line
short of length on off stump, Morgan gets right behind it and defends it to the off side
short delivery on the body, fended off towards square leg
he bowls it full on the pads and with the fine leg up, that is criminal. Bell punishes it by flicking it to deep backward square leg boundary
tossed up on off, he thrusts his front foot out and drives it to long-on
fuller on off and middle, Bell drives it to long-off
he plays it to deep midwicket with the spin
slower this time, Bell drops it with soft hands to the off side and sets off for a quick single
turns in to the leg side, but plays it straight to midwicket
on the middle and leg, helped on its way down to fine leg
length ball outside off, Morgan tries to push it through off side, but gets an inside edge towards midwicket
he gets his shot right this time as he punches it to deep extra cover off the front foot.
tries to leave the length delivery outside off, but is late and the ball hits the bat and drops on the off side. Lucky there. Could have gone anywhere
length ball outside off, he takes a good big stride and pushes it to cover
fuller length outside off, driven on the up towards cover, but Raina makes an excellent diving save to restrict the batsman to just one
time for Bell to tong! It is a full length ball and he drives it without much fuss over mid-off, the ball almost goes all the way.
of off and turning in, Morgan plays it with a closed face to the leg side, toward deep midwicket
floated outside off, Bell drives it on the up through cover point for a single
quicker and fuller outside off, defended towards midwicket
another quicker delivery on off, defended back to the bowler
he sees the batsman shuffle and fires it down the leg side, too far down though
gets his line back, defended back to the bowler
he shuffles across and flicks this one on middle and leg down to fine leg
flighted on a length, on off stump, Morgan defends off the front foot
pushed further up, more front foot defence by Morgan
flighted outside off, the batman comes forward and drives to long off
bowls a slider across the right-hander, it goes past he outside edge
on the middle stump this time, Bell tickles it down to deep backward square leg
goes back and punches the flat delivery to deep point
length ball on off, Morgan dabs it to point, Kohli there, but takes a quick single and both make it comfortably
takes a step down the pitch, gets beside the line of the short of length ball and guides it to third man
short and wide, Morgan times his cut but he is unable to beat a flying Kohli at point. Super stop to his right, saves a certain boundary
fuller length ball on off and middle, Bell drives it hard, but it's hit straight to mid-on
slightly slower at 124 ks, it was short of length outside off and the lack of pace buggered the timing.
friendly full-toss on off stump, driven down to long-off
he quickly changes his stances and picks up this low full toss from leg stump and reverse sweeps it to the point boundary
on the middle and leg, punched to deep midwicket for a single
flatter delivery, pushes Morgan back, defended back to the bowler
he goes back to a flatter one outside off and tucks it towards wide mid-on
another low full-toss on the pads and Bell easily flicks it to deep square leg for a couple
this one pitches on middle and leg and turns down the leg side, was bowled with a slightly round-arm action
fuller delivery on the middle stump, driven to long-on for a single
length ball outside off, driven on the up to extra cover, who picks it up and throws down the stumps at non-striker's, but that gives away overthrows
short of length on the middle, Morgan stays on the back foot and turns it to deep midwicket
slower offcutter outside off, Bell drops it in front of cover and takes off for a quick single as the fielder is standing on the edge of the circle
fuller length on the stump, driven on the up to deep cover
Oh yes!! and how nicely is that done! It is a full-toss on the pads, and he drives it crisply through the on side to bring up the first century of this series
slower ball on the middle stump, and on length, defended back down the pitch
fuller delivery on off and middle, Morgan jabs at it with a lot of bottom-hand and it travel over long-on so easily. Beautifully timed
on the off side, he cuts it straight to point
slower delivery on the middle, defended off the front foot
goes for the sweep, but doesn't get hold of it and almost drags it to the leg stump, the ball rolls past Dhoni and they take a single
flighted delivery on off and middle, it is flicked through to deep midwicket
attempts the sweep again, but is nowhere near the pitch of the ball, gets hit on the front pad, but outside the line of off
short of length ball outside off, Bell plays a forehand down the line to long-off
Wallop!! fuller delivery outside off, no half-measures from him, cracks it over long-off with a full swing of the bat
short of length delivery outside off, he opens the face, but straight to point
shuffles across and flicks the full delivery on the off and middle through square leg. There is no one at the deep, so backward square has to pull it back
it's getting hot in here! Short ball, Morgan pulls it flat and deep into the stands at deep backward square
fuller delivery outside off, Morgan bunts it on the pitch, the ball then bounces over the head of the bowler and they take a single
short of length outside off, Morgan guides it to third man
runs coming in thick and fast now. He gets a full delivery on the pads and beautifully drives it past a diving midwicket all the way to the boundary
short of length on off, defended to the leg side
slower ball on a length outside off, Bell gets beside the line and dabs it to the left of backward point
length ball on off stump this time, defended towards cover
in the channel outside off, Bell stretches forward and pushes it to deep cover for a single. He is doing it easily
easily done! fuller delivery on off stump and Bell sweetly times it through extra cover, the fielder at the deep didn't really make an effort, but a gorgeous drive nonetheless
Bell takes his team home by dabbing the ball on the off side and completing a comfortable win
